-- Osmond Plans Investment Vehicle to Raise Funds, Telegraph Says
-- B y   N a n d i n i   S u k u m a r
-- 2012-01-01T16:41:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-01/osmond-plans-investment-vehicle-to-raise-funds-telegraph-says.html
Hugh Osmond , who founded U.K.
restaurant chain Pizza Express, plans a successor to his Horizon
investment vehicle, the Sunday Telegraph  reported , citing
unidentified sources close to the British entrepreneur.  Osmond is planning a special purpose acquisition company to
raise about 500 million pounds ($777.2 million), the paper said.  Osmond declined to comment, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nandini Sukumar in London at 
 nsukumar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
